# Presto (Ontario public transit payment card)

## Description
The Presto card (or PRESTO) is an electronic fare payment system used on participating public transit systems in the province of Ontario. As of August 2018, PRESTO is used on public transit in the Greater Toronto Area, Hamilton, and Ottawa.

PRESTO may collect personal information about users in connection with their use of the transit card, including information about financial transactions, address or phone number, and travel history. [[source](https://www.prestocard.ca/en/privacy)]

## Do I legally own the data this org has about me?
### Unclear

## Can I see all the data they have about me, for free?
### Yes
"You may request access to your personal information at any time" although there are some cases where PRESTO reserves the right to refuse access (eg. if your records contain references to other people). [[source](https://www.prestocard.ca/en/privacy)]

You can also access your travel history online by downloading your Transit Usage Report. [[source](https://www.prestocard.ca/en/about/FAQ/tax-credit)]
